## Phrases and patterns to avoid

<!-- Universal anti-patterns. These apply regardless of surface. Add personal ones below the list. -->

- "I hope this message finds you well."
- "Just wanted to reach out to..."
- "Per my last message..."
- "Circling back..."
- "Leverage" as a verb (unless literal).
- "Synergy," "stakeholders," "value-add," "low-hanging fruit."
- Apology pile-ups ("So sorry for the delay, really apologize, I know you've been waiting...")
- Overly hedged claims that drain the sentence of meaning ("It's possible that in some cases this might...")
- Starting with weather, wishing, or vibes ("Hope your week is going well!", "Happy Monday!")

